{"parse":{"title":"Akio Kanai","pageid":54532662,"revid":826190728,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>Dr. <b>Akio Kanai</b><span style=\"font-weight: normal\">&#32;(<span lang=\"ja\">\u91d1\u4e95 \u662d\u96c4</span><span style=\"display:none\">,</span>&#32;<i>Kanai Akio</i>)</span> is the CEO of Fuji Optical in Hokkaido Japan, and the recipient of the 2006 <a href=\"/wiki/Nansen_Refugee_Award\" title=\"Nansen Refugee Award\">Nansen Refugee Award</a>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Early_life\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Early life</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Career\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Career</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Work_with_refugees_and_internally_displaced_people\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Work with refugees and internally displaced people</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Awards\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Awards</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Early_life\">Early life</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Akio_Kanai&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Early life\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Kanai was born in 1942 on the northern Pacific island of <a href=\"/wiki/Sakhalin\" title=\"Sakhalin\">Sakhalin</a>. He was forcibly replaced as a child in the turmoil of the end of WWII and moved to Japan. His early life experiences forever shaped his perception of internally displaced people and refugees.<sup id=\"cite_ref-UNHCR_Biography_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-UNHCR_Biography-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Career\">Career</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Akio_Kanai&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Career\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>He studied for a business degree at <a href=\"/wiki/Waseda_University\" title=\"Waseda University\">Waseda University</a> in <a href=\"/wiki/Tokyo\" title=\"Tokyo\">Tokyo</a>. In 1966 he decided to study a second subject and enrolled at the Southern California College of Optometry and graduated in 1972 as a doctor. After visiting Hopi Indians in Arizona and helping them improve their vision by distributing spectacles he realized that he wanted to continue on the pathway of humanitarian work. He returned to Japan in 1973 to work in the family concern  Fuji Optical at <a href=\"/wiki/Hokkaido\" title=\"Hokkaido\">Hokkaido</a>. In 1996 he became the president of the company. In 2006 he was the CEO and chairman of Fuji Optical.<sup id=\"cite_ref-UNHCR_Biography_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-UNHCR_Biography-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Work_with_refugees_and_internally_displaced_people\">Work with refugees and internally displaced people</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Akio_Kanai&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Work with refugees and internally displaced people\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Dr. Akio Kanai began his work with refugees in 1983 in Thailand with <a href=\"/wiki/Indochina_refugee_crisis\" title=\"Indochina refugee crisis\">indochinese refugees</a>. Many of the refugees with impaired eye sight had lost or broken their glasses in the process of fleeing. They were though in desperate need to see clearly as they had to undergo courses ahead of being resettled and neede to study. He checked their eye sight so that the refugees could receive the right kind of glasses and see clearly again.<sup id=\"cite_ref-UNHCR_Biography_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-UNHCR_Biography-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\nHe began cooperating with <a href=\"/wiki/UNHCR\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"UNHCR\">UNHCR</a> in 1984 and conducted over 24 mission in <a href=\"/wiki/Azerbaijan\" title=\"Azerbaijan\">Azerbaijan</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Armenia\" title=\"Armenia\">Armenia</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Thailand\" title=\"Thailand\">Thailand</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Nepal\" title=\"Nepal\">Nepal</a>. Overall he made cash granst of over 75.000 US$, trained local medial staff, provided <a href=\"/wiki/Optometry\" title=\"Optometry\">optometry</a> equipment and donated more than 108.200 pairs of glasses. Fuji Optical is UNHCR's longest-serving corporate partner. \nDr. Kanai further involved his company and employees in the Optical Vision Aid Mission. Over 70 of his employees have taken part in the missions using their holidays to assist in the refugee camps.<sup id=\"cite_ref-UNHCR_Biography_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-UNHCR_Biography-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\nIn 2006 he was awarded with the prestigious <a href=\"/wiki/Nansen_Refugee_Award\" title=\"Nansen Refugee Award\">Nansen Refugee Award</a> for his efforts in helping to improve the vision of refugees.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Nansen_Refugee_Award_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Nansen_Refugee_Award-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> He vowed to pour the prize money of 100.000 $ back into his humanitarian work in Armenia and Azerbaijan.<sup id=\"cite_ref-UN_News_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-UN_News-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\nDuring his acceptance speech for the award Dr. Kanai said: \u201cthe award is testimony to the significance that the role of optometry plays in the future of refugees by improving their sight and this empowering them to secure a \u2018future in focus\u2019\u2026 Eyesight can change one\u2019s life. My dream is that a simple pair of glasses can change the lives of refugees and internally displaced persons (IDPs) for the better.\u201d<sup id=\"cite_ref-UN_News_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-UN_News-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> <sup id=\"cite_ref-UNHCR,_the_UN_Refugee_Agency_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-UNHCR,_the_UN_Refugee_Agency-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>By 2016 he had improved the sight of more than 130.000 displaced people.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Awards\">Awards</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Akio_Kanai&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: Awards\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Nansen_Refugee_Award\" title=\"Nansen Refugee Award\">Nansen Refugee Award</a> 2006 <sup id=\"cite_ref-Nansen_Refugee_Award_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Nansen_Refugee_Award-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Akio_Kanai&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-UNHCR_Biography-1\"><span class=\"mw-ci